The identify command confirms that the image is indeed in grayscale. Now let me proceed with counting objects (coins, enemies, turtles) in each frame using the object_counter skill.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The identify command confirms that keyframes_001.png is in grayscale. Now I need to count objects in each frame. I'll use the object_counter skill to count coins, enemies, and turtles in each of the 8 keyframes.",
  "plan": "Use the object_counter skill to count objects in each keyframe. The skill uses a python script (count_objects.py) that takes an input image and an object image, and outputs the count of the object in the image. I'll need to run this script for each keyframe and each object type (coin, enemy, turtle).",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /root/.claude/skills/object_counter/scripts/count_objects.py --tool count --input_image /root/keyframes_001.png --object_image /root/coin.png --threshold 0.9 --dedup_min_dist 3\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ]
}
```
